Shut your mouth fool.

[quote=“Million5, post:1, topic:324979”]Plzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz
I cant play on servers!!! I need some1 to know how to get it fix!!!
IF YOU GOT TEAMVIEAWER THEN TALK TO ME AND FIND OUT WHATS THE PROBLEM!![/quote]
Java appears to be installed and probably functioning correctly, but Java cannot find the classes you referenced in your batch file. This often simply means that you’re executing from the wrong directory, so you can either add something like “cd ./files/” just above the “java something etc” line, or you can post your entire batch file here and hope someone does it for you
